6316 /// PseudoObjectExpr - An expression which accesses a pseudo-object
6317 /// l-value. A pseudo-object is an abstract object, accesses to which
6318 /// are translated to calls. The pseudo-object expression has a
6319 /// syntactic form, which shows how the expression was actually
6320 /// written in the source code, and a semantic form, which is a series
6321 /// of expressions to be executed in order which detail how the
6322 /// operation is actually evaluated. Optionally, one of the semantic
6323 /// forms may also provide a result value for the expression.
6324 ///
6325 /// If any of the semantic-form expressions is an OpaqueValueExpr,
6326 /// that OVE is required to have a source expression, and it is bound
6327 /// to the result of that source expression. Such OVEs may appear
6328 /// only in subsequent semantic-form expressions and as
6329 /// sub-expressions of the syntactic form.
6330 ///
6331 /// PseudoObjectExpr should be used only when an operation can be
6332 /// usefully described in terms of fairly simple rewrite rules on
6333 /// objects and functions that are meant to be used by end-developers.
6334 /// For example, under the Itanium ABI, dynamic casts are implemented
6335 /// as a call to a runtime function called __dynamic_cast; using this
6336 /// class to describe that would be inappropriate because that call is
6337 /// not really part of the user-visible semantics, and instead the
6338 /// cast is properly reflected in the AST and IR-generation has been
6339 /// taught to generate the call as necessary. In contrast, an
6340 /// Objective-C property access is semantically defined to be
6341 /// equivalent to a particular message send, and this is very much
6342 /// part of the user model. The name of this class encourages this
6343 /// modelling design.
6344 class PseudoObjectExpr final
6345  : public Expr,
6346  private llvm::TrailingObjects<PseudoObjectExpr, Expr *> {
6347  // PseudoObjectExprBits.NumSubExprs - The number of sub-expressions.
6348  // Always at least two, because the first sub-expression is the
6349  // syntactic form.
6350 
6351  // PseudoObjectExprBits.ResultIndex - The index of the
6352  // sub-expression holding the result. 0 means the result is void,
6353  // which is unambiguous because it's the index of the syntactic
6354  // form. Note that this is therefore 1 higher than the value passed
6355  // in to Create, which is an index within the semantic forms.
6356  // Note also that ASTStmtWriter assumes this encoding.
6357 
6358  Expr **getSubExprsBuffer() { return getTrailingObjects<Expr *>(); }
6359  const Expr * const *getSubExprsBuffer() const {
6360  return getTrailingObjects<Expr *>();
6361  }
6362 
6363  PseudoObjectExpr(QualType type, ExprValueKind VK,
6364  Expr *syntactic, ArrayRef<Expr*> semantic,
6365  unsigned resultIndex);
6366 
6367  PseudoObjectExpr(EmptyShell shell, unsigned numSemanticExprs);
6368 
6369  unsigned getNumSubExprs() const {
6370  return PseudoObjectExprBits.NumSubExprs;
6371  }
6372 
6373 public:
6374  /// NoResult - A value for the result index indicating that there is
6375  /// no semantic result.
6376  enum : unsigned { NoResult = ~0U };
6377 
6378  static PseudoObjectExpr *Create(const ASTContext &Context, Expr *syntactic,
6379  ArrayRef<Expr*> semantic,
6380  unsigned resultIndex);
6381 
6382  static PseudoObjectExpr *Create(const ASTContext &Context, EmptyShell shell,
6383  unsigned numSemanticExprs);
6384 
6385  /// Return the syntactic form of this expression, i.e. the
6386  /// expression it actually looks like. Likely to be expressed in
6387  /// terms of OpaqueValueExprs bound in the semantic form.
6388  Expr *getSyntacticForm() { return getSubExprsBuffer()[0]; }
6389  const Expr *getSyntacticForm() const { return getSubExprsBuffer()[0]; }
6390 
6391  /// Return the index of the result-bearing expression into the semantics
6392  /// expressions, or PseudoObjectExpr::NoResult if there is none.
6393  unsigned getResultExprIndex() const {
6394  if (PseudoObjectExprBits.ResultIndex == 0) return NoResult;
6395  return PseudoObjectExprBits.ResultIndex - 1;
6396  }
6397 
6398  /// Return the result-bearing expression, or null if there is none.
6399  Expr *getResultExpr() {
6400  if (PseudoObjectExprBits.ResultIndex == 0)
6401  return nullptr;
6402  return getSubExprsBuffer()[PseudoObjectExprBits.ResultIndex];
6403  }
6404  const Expr *getResultExpr() const {
6405  return const_cast<PseudoObjectExpr*>(this)->getResultExpr();
6406  }
6407 
6408  unsigned getNumSemanticExprs() const { return getNumSubExprs() - 1; }
6409 
6410  typedef Expr * const *semantics_iterator;
6411  typedef const Expr * const *const_semantics_iterator;
6412  semantics_iterator semantics_begin() {
6413  return getSubExprsBuffer() + 1;
6414  }
6415  const_semantics_iterator semantics_begin() const {
6416  return getSubExprsBuffer() + 1;
6417  }
6418  semantics_iterator semantics_end() {
6419  return getSubExprsBuffer() + getNumSubExprs();
6420  }
6421  const_semantics_iterator semantics_end() const {
6422  return getSubExprsBuffer() + getNumSubExprs();
6423  }
6424 
6425  ArrayRef<Expr*> semantics() {
6426  return ArrayRef(semantics_begin(), semantics_end());
6427  }
6428  ArrayRef<const Expr*> semantics() const {
6429  return ArrayRef(semantics_begin(), semantics_end());
6430  }
6431 
6432  Expr *getSemanticExpr(unsigned index) {
6433  assert(index + 1 < getNumSubExprs());
6434  return getSubExprsBuffer()[index + 1];
6435  }
6436  const Expr *getSemanticExpr(unsigned index) const {
6437  return const_cast<PseudoObjectExpr*>(this)->getSemanticExpr(index);
6438  }
6439 
6440  SourceLocation getExprLoc() const LLVM_READONLY {
6441  return getSyntacticForm()->getExprLoc();
6442  }
6443 
6444  SourceLocation getBeginLoc() const LLVM_READONLY {
6445  return getSyntacticForm()->getBeginLoc();
6446  }
6447  SourceLocation getEndLoc() const LLVM_READONLY {
6448  return getSyntacticForm()->getEndLoc();
6449  }
6450 
6451  child_range children() {
6452  const_child_range CCR =
6453  const_cast<const PseudoObjectExpr *>(this)->children();
6454  return child_range(cast_away_const(CCR.begin()),
6455  cast_away_const(CCR.end()));
6456  }
6457  const_child_range children() const {
6458  Stmt *const *cs = const_cast<Stmt *const *>(
6459  reinterpret_cast<const Stmt *const *>(getSubExprsBuffer()));
6460  return const_child_range(cs, cs + getNumSubExprs());
6461  }
6462 
6463  static bool classof(const Stmt *T) {
6464  return T->getStmtClass() == PseudoObjectExprClass;
6465  }
6466 
6467  friend TrailingObjects;
6468  friend class ASTStmtReader;
6469 };

6471 /// AtomicExpr - Variadic atomic builtins: __atomic_exchange, __atomic_fetch_*,
6472 /// __atomic_load, __atomic_store, and __atomic_compare_exchange_*, for the
6473 /// similarly-named C++11 instructions, and __c11 variants for <stdatomic.h>,
6474 /// and corresponding __opencl_atomic_* for OpenCL 2.0.
6475 /// All of these instructions take one primary pointer, at least one memory
6476 /// order. The instructions for which getScopeModel returns non-null value
6477 /// take one synch scope.
6478 class AtomicExpr : public Expr {
6479 public:
6480  enum AtomicOp {
6481 #define BUILTIN(ID, TYPE, ATTRS)
6482 #define ATOMIC_BUILTIN(ID, TYPE, ATTRS) AO ## ID,
6483 #include "clang/Basic/Builtins.inc"
6484  // Avoid trailing comma
6485  BI_First = 0
6486  };
6487 
6488 private:
6489  /// Location of sub-expressions.
6490  /// The location of Scope sub-expression is NumSubExprs - 1, which is
6491  /// not fixed, therefore is not defined in enum.
6492  enum { PTR, ORDER, VAL1, ORDER_FAIL, VAL2, WEAK, END_EXPR };
6493  Stmt *SubExprs[END_EXPR + 1];
6494  unsigned NumSubExprs;
6495  SourceLocation BuiltinLoc, RParenLoc;
6496  AtomicOp Op;
6497 
6498  friend class ASTStmtReader;
6499 public:
6500  AtomicExpr(SourceLocation BLoc, ArrayRef<Expr*> args, QualType t,
6501  AtomicOp op, SourceLocation RP);
6502 
6503  /// Determine the number of arguments the specified atomic builtin
6504  /// should have.
6505  static unsigned getNumSubExprs(AtomicOp Op);
6506 
6507  /// Build an empty AtomicExpr.
6508  explicit AtomicExpr(EmptyShell Empty) : Expr(AtomicExprClass, Empty) { }
6509 
6510  Expr *getPtr() const {
6511  return cast<Expr>(SubExprs[PTR]);
6512  }
6513  Expr *getOrder() const {
6514  return cast<Expr>(SubExprs[ORDER]);
6515  }
6516  Expr *getScope() const {
6517  assert(getScopeModel() && "No scope");
6518  return cast<Expr>(SubExprs[NumSubExprs - 1]);
6519  }
6520  Expr *getVal1() const {
6521  if (Op == AO__c11_atomic_init || Op == AO__opencl_atomic_init)
6522  return cast<Expr>(SubExprs[ORDER]);
6523  assert(NumSubExprs > VAL1);
6524  return cast<Expr>(SubExprs[VAL1]);
6525  }
6526  Expr *getOrderFail() const {
6527  assert(NumSubExprs > ORDER_FAIL);
6528  return cast<Expr>(SubExprs[ORDER_FAIL]);
6529  }
6530  Expr *getVal2() const {
6531  if (Op == AO__atomic_exchange || Op == AO__scoped_atomic_exchange)
6532  return cast<Expr>(SubExprs[ORDER_FAIL]);
6533  assert(NumSubExprs > VAL2);
6534  return cast<Expr>(SubExprs[VAL2]);
6535  }
6536  Expr *getWeak() const {
6537  assert(NumSubExprs > WEAK);
6538  return cast<Expr>(SubExprs[WEAK]);
6539  }
6540  QualType getValueType() const;
6541 
6542  AtomicOp getOp() const { return Op; }
6543  StringRef getOpAsString() const {
6544  switch (Op) {
6545 #define BUILTIN(ID, TYPE, ATTRS)
6546 #define ATOMIC_BUILTIN(ID, TYPE, ATTRS) \
6547  case AO##ID: \
6548  return #ID;
6549 #include "clang/Basic/Builtins.inc"
6550  }
6551  llvm_unreachable("not an atomic operator?");
6552  }
6553  unsigned getNumSubExprs() const { return NumSubExprs; }
6554 
6555  Expr **getSubExprs() { return reinterpret_cast<Expr **>(SubExprs); }
6556  const Expr * const *getSubExprs() const {
6557  return reinterpret_cast<Expr * const *>(SubExprs);
6558  }
6559 
6560  bool isVolatile() const {
6561  return getPtr()->getType()->getPointeeType().isVolatileQualified();
6562  }
6563 
6564  bool isCmpXChg() const {
6565  return getOp() == AO__c11_atomic_compare_exchange_strong ||
6566  getOp() == AO__c11_atomic_compare_exchange_weak ||
6567  getOp() == AO__hip_atomic_compare_exchange_strong ||
6568  getOp() == AO__opencl_atomic_compare_exchange_strong ||
6569  getOp() == AO__opencl_atomic_compare_exchange_weak ||
6570  getOp() == AO__hip_atomic_compare_exchange_weak ||
6571  getOp() == AO__atomic_compare_exchange ||
6572  getOp() == AO__atomic_compare_exchange_n ||
6573  getOp() == AO__scoped_atomic_compare_exchange ||
6574  getOp() == AO__scoped_atomic_compare_exchange_n;
6575  }
6576 
6577  bool isOpenCL() const {
6578  return getOp() >= AO__opencl_atomic_compare_exchange_strong &&
6579  getOp() <= AO__opencl_atomic_store;
6580  }
6581 
6582  SourceLocation getBuiltinLoc() const { return BuiltinLoc; }
6583  SourceLocation getRParenLoc() const { return RParenLoc; }
6584 
6585  SourceLocation getBeginLoc() const LLVM_READONLY { return BuiltinLoc; }
6586  SourceLocation getEndLoc() const LLVM_READONLY { return RParenLoc; }
6587 
6588  static bool classof(const Stmt *T) {
6589  return T->getStmtClass() == AtomicExprClass;
6590  }
6591 
6592  // Iterators
6593  child_range children() {
6594  return child_range(SubExprs, SubExprs+NumSubExprs);
6595  }
6596  const_child_range children() const {
6597  return const_child_range(SubExprs, SubExprs + NumSubExprs);
6598  }
6599 
6600  /// Get atomic scope model for the atomic op code.
6601  /// \return empty atomic scope model if the atomic op code does not have
6602  /// scope operand.
6603  static std::unique_ptr<AtomicScopeModel> getScopeModel(AtomicOp Op) {
6604  // FIXME: Allow grouping of builtins to be able to only check >= and <=
6605  if (Op >= AO__opencl_atomic_compare_exchange_strong &&
6606  Op <= AO__opencl_atomic_store && Op != AO__opencl_atomic_init)
6607  return AtomicScopeModel::create(AtomicScopeModelKind::OpenCL);
6608  if (Op >= AO__hip_atomic_compare_exchange_strong &&
6609  Op <= AO__hip_atomic_store)
6610  return AtomicScopeModel::create(AtomicScopeModelKind::HIP);
6611  if (Op >= AO__scoped_atomic_add_fetch && Op <= AO__scoped_atomic_xor_fetch)
6612  return AtomicScopeModel::create(AtomicScopeModelKind::Generic);
6613  return AtomicScopeModel::create(AtomicScopeModelKind::None);
6614  }
6615 
6616  /// Get atomic scope model.
6617  /// \return empty atomic scope model if this atomic expression does not have
6618  /// scope operand.
6619  std::unique_ptr<AtomicScopeModel> getScopeModel() const {
6620  return getScopeModel(getOp());
6621  }
6622 };

6624 /// TypoExpr - Internal placeholder for expressions where typo correction
6625 /// still needs to be performed and/or an error diagnostic emitted.
6626 class TypoExpr : public Expr {
6627  // The location for the typo name.
6628  SourceLocation TypoLoc;
6629 
6630 public:
6631  TypoExpr(QualType T, SourceLocation TypoLoc)
6632  : Expr(TypoExprClass, T, VK_LValue, OK_Ordinary), TypoLoc(TypoLoc) {
6633  assert(T->isDependentType() && "TypoExpr given a non-dependent type");
6634  setDependence(ExprDependence::TypeValueInstantiation |
6635  ExprDependence::Error);
6636  }
6637 
6638  child_range children() {
6639  return child_range(child_iterator(), child_iterator());
6640  }
6641  const_child_range children() const {
6642  return const_child_range(const_child_iterator(), const_child_iterator());
6643  }
6644 
6645  SourceLocation getBeginLoc() const LLVM_READONLY { return TypoLoc; }
6646  SourceLocation getEndLoc() const LLVM_READONLY { return TypoLoc; }
6647 
6648  static bool classof(const Stmt *T) {
6649  return T->getStmtClass() == TypoExprClass;
6650  }
6651 
6652 };

6654 /// Frontend produces RecoveryExprs on semantic errors that prevent creating
6655 /// other well-formed expressions. E.g. when type-checking of a binary operator
6656 /// fails, we cannot produce a BinaryOperator expression. Instead, we can choose
6657 /// to produce a recovery expression storing left and right operands.
6658 ///
6659 /// RecoveryExpr does not have any semantic meaning in C++, it is only useful to
6660 /// preserve expressions in AST that would otherwise be dropped. It captures
6661 /// subexpressions of some expression that we could not construct and source
6662 /// range covered by the expression.
6663 ///
6664 /// By default, RecoveryExpr uses dependence-bits to take advantage of existing
6665 /// machinery to deal with dependent code in C++, e.g. RecoveryExpr is preserved
6666 /// in `decltype(<broken-expr>)` as part of the `DependentDecltypeType`. In
6667 /// addition to that, clang does not report most errors on dependent
6668 /// expressions, so we get rid of bogus errors for free. However, note that
6669 /// unlike other dependent expressions, RecoveryExpr can be produced in
6670 /// non-template contexts.
6671 ///
6672 /// We will preserve the type in RecoveryExpr when the type is known, e.g.
6673 /// preserving the return type for a broken non-overloaded function call, a
6674 /// overloaded call where all candidates have the same return type. In this
6675 /// case, the expression is not type-dependent (unless the known type is itself
6676 /// dependent)
6677 ///
6678 /// One can also reliably suppress all bogus errors on expressions containing
6679 /// recovery expressions by examining results of Expr::containsErrors().
6680 class RecoveryExpr final : public Expr,
6681  private llvm::TrailingObjects<RecoveryExpr, Expr *> {
6682 public:
6683  static RecoveryExpr *Create(ASTContext &Ctx, QualType T,
6684  SourceLocation BeginLoc, SourceLocation EndLoc,
6685  ArrayRef<Expr *> SubExprs);
6686  static RecoveryExpr *CreateEmpty(ASTContext &Ctx, unsigned NumSubExprs);
6687 
6688  ArrayRef<Expr *> subExpressions() {
6689  auto *B = getTrailingObjects<Expr *>();
6690  return llvm::ArrayRef(B, B + NumExprs);
6691  }
6692 
6693  ArrayRef<const Expr *> subExpressions() const {
6694  return const_cast<RecoveryExpr *>(this)->subExpressions();
6695  }
6696 
6697  child_range children() {
6698  Stmt **B = reinterpret_cast<Stmt **>(getTrailingObjects<Expr *>());
6699  return child_range(B, B + NumExprs);
6700  }
6701 
6702  SourceLocation getBeginLoc() const { return BeginLoc; }
6703  SourceLocation getEndLoc() const { return EndLoc; }
6704 
6705  static bool classof(const Stmt *T) {
6706  return T->getStmtClass() == RecoveryExprClass;
6707  }
6708 
6709 private:
6710  RecoveryExpr(ASTContext &Ctx, QualType T, SourceLocation BeginLoc,
6711  SourceLocation EndLoc, ArrayRef<Expr *> SubExprs);
6712  RecoveryExpr(EmptyShell Empty, unsigned NumSubExprs)
6713  : Expr(RecoveryExprClass, Empty), NumExprs(NumSubExprs) {}
6714 
6715  size_t numTrailingObjects(OverloadToken<Stmt *>) const { return NumExprs; }
6716 
6717  SourceLocation BeginLoc, EndLoc;
6718  unsigned NumExprs;
6719  friend TrailingObjects;
6720  friend class ASTStmtReader;
6721  friend class ASTStmtWriter;
6722 };
6723 
6724 } // end namespace clang
